 the following primary pieces of equipment:

- a 12,000-gallon bulk storage AST (for CP-80 liquid), stored on the exterior of the site, that is filled to a maximum of 85% of its volumetric capacity (10,200 gallons);

- distribution and transfer piping that supply CP-80 to a metering unit that is located within the building in a bulk material storage room;

- a metering unit that measures, controls, and supplies a precise amount of blowing agent downstream towards the foam injection mixhead;

- distribution piping that transfers the CP-80 from the metering unit out to the process line, where the foam mixhead is located; and,

- a continuous pour foaming mixhead that includes a conveyor system.



The process also includes other utility, auxiliary, and support systems that enable very precise control of the covered chemical's parameters (temperature, pressure, etc.).



Above all else, TrueCore values the safety and health of its employees, those located in close proximity to the site, and protection of the environment - both on-site and off-site. To ensure that this covered polyurethane foaming process remains in a safe state at all times and that the opportunity for covered chemical to release outside of the process and equipment is absolutely minimized, TrueCore's process equipment and support systems were designed, constructed, and installed with a "Safety First" mentality.  In addition to the process and equipment being designed inherently safe, the facility will employ numerous safety systems to prevent an unintended release of chemical.  Specifically, process- and support-related safety systems that have been installed and used associated with the covered process include the following:

